## Social Behaviour

**Kuhli Loaches are obligate group animals.** A single Kuhli Loach will be invisible, stressed, and prone to disease. The minimum group size is **6 individuals**; 8–12 is better.

In groups, Kuhli Loaches display their natural social behaviour:
- **Pile sleeping** — Groups of 4–8 loaches pile together in shared hiding spots, bodies intertwined. This is normal and healthy behaviour, not distress.
- **Night activity** — After lights out, groups emerge and forage actively across the substrate
- **Playful interaction** — Groups will chase each other briefly in what appears to be play behaviour, particularly during feeding

Solitary Kuhli Loaches hide completely, eat poorly, and typically die earlier than group-kept individuals.

