## Nocturnal Behaviour and "Disappearing Fish" Syndrome

New Kuhli Loach keepers almost universally experience alarm when their fish seem to disappear. The fish are:
- Buried in substrate (sometimes several centimetres deep)
- Hidden inside decorations, pipes, or filter housing
- Wedged between equipment and the tank wall
- Sleeping in a pile under leaf litter

This is completely normal. Kuhli Loaches can remain buried for 24–48 hours at a time. The easiest way to confirm they're alive: feed after lights out and observe with red light (minimal disruption) or IR. If you see loaches emerge within 10–15 minutes of adding food, all is well.

A Kuhli Loach that never emerges at night after weeks is a sign of illness, poor tankmate compatibility, or suboptimal parameters.

