## The "New Tank" Stress Period

Newly acquired Kuhli Loaches are particularly vulnerable to stress during the first 2–4 weeks in a new tank. During this time they may:
- Refuse food completely
- Remain buried for days at a time
- Show signs of ich (stress triggers ich outbreaks in susceptible fish)
- Press against filter intakes or other unusual spots

Give them time. A well-planted, covered tank with correct parameters and a group of 6+ will see them settle within 3–4 weeks.

